OL,6,FThe BBC World Service was originally
OL,7,Ffunded through the Foreign and
OL,8,FCommonwealth Office. This changed
OL,9,Fduring the first licence fee freeze
OL,10,Fthat ran from 2011 to 2016, when the
OL,11,FBBC was asked to shoulder the cost of
OL,12,FS4C, the World Service and the rollout
OL,13,Fof local TV in addition to funding its
OL,14,Fown services.
OL,16,FThe Government currently pays #94.4
OL,17,Fmillion a year towards the World
OL,18,FService as part of a three-year #283.2m
OL,19,Fagreement, but that amounts to less
OL,20,Fthan a quarter of the World Service's
OL,21,Ftotal annual budget.
